extremeNPMib.name: extremeNPMib
extremeNPMib.description: Extreme NP objects: NP card information

extremeNPModuleTable.name: extremeNPModuleTable
extremeNPModuleTable.description: A table containing information about each Intelligent module in the chassis.

extremeNPModuleEntry.name: extremeNPModuleEntry
extremeNPModuleEntry.description: A table entry containing information about the intelligent modules configured in the chassis. This table does not contain rows for the slots which do not have a network processor based module.

extremeNPModuleSlotNumber.name: extremeNPModuleSlotNumber
extremeNPModuleSlotNumber.description: A unique integer identifying the particular slot in the chassis.

extremeNPModuleDescription.name: extremeNPModuleDescription
extremeNPModuleDescription.description: A description of the particular slot in the chassis.

extremeNPModuleCurrentSoftware.name: extremeNPModuleCurrentSoftware
extremeNPModuleCurrentSoftware.description: The version of the software currently running on the module.

extremeNPModulePrimarySoftware.name: extremeNPModulePrimarySoftware
extremeNPModulePrimarySoftware.description: The version of software in the primary image of the module.

extremeNPModuleSecondarySoftware.name: extremeNPModuleSecondarySoftware
extremeNPModuleSecondarySoftware.description: The version of software in the secondary image of the module.

extremeNPModuleBootromVersion.name: extremeNPModuleBootromVersion
extremeNPModuleBootromVersion.description: The version of bootrom that the module will use when restarting.

extremeNPModuleProcessorState.name: extremeNPModuleProcessorState
extremeNPModuleProcessorState.description: An Octet String indicating the status of the various processors on an Intelligent Module. Each byte in the Octet String represents state for one processor. For the Avalanche based PoS and ARM modules, the first byte (from MSB) represents the state of the General Purpose Processor, the second byte the state of Network Processor 1, and the third byte the state of Network Processor 2 and so on. A value of 0 in each byte indicates that the Processor is not operational, while a value 1 indicates that it is.

extremeSMAUpTime.name: extremeSMAUpTime

extremeSMAQosBroadcaster.name: extremeSMAQosBroadcaster

extremeSMANumFromBroadcaster.name: extremeSMANumFromBroadcaster

extremeSMANumToListener.name: extremeSMANumToListener

extremeSMABytesBroadcaster.name: extremeSMABytesBroadcaster

extremeSMABytesListener.name: extremeSMABytesListener
extremeSMABytesListener.description: The total number of data bytes sent to listeners.

extremeMplsTlsTable.name: extremeMplsTlsTable
extremeMplsTlsTable.description: A table containing information about each MPLS TLS tunnel in the chassis.

extremeMplsTlsEntry.name: extremeMplsTlsEntry
extremeMplsTlsEntry.description: A table entry containing information about the MPLS TLS tunnel.

extremeMplsTlsNum.name: extremeMplsTlsNum
extremeMplsTlsNum.description: An index used to reference each configured TLS tunnel.

extremeMplsTlsName.name: extremeMplsTlsName
extremeMplsTlsName.description: The user defined TLS tunnel identifier name.

extremeMplsTlsLocalIpAddr.name: extremeMplsTlsLocalIpAddr
extremeMplsTlsLocalIpAddr.description: The TLS tunnel local endpoint IP address, only valid if TLS tunnel is Dynamic. Otherwise, this field is set to zero.

extremeMplsTlsPeerIpAddr.name: extremeMplsTlsPeerIpAddr
extremeMplsTlsPeerIpAddr.description: The TLS tunnel peer endpoint IP address.

extremeMplsTlsDynamic.name: extremeMplsTlsDynamic
extremeMplsTlsDynamic.description: Flag indicating that the TLS tunnel is Dynamic. If set, the TLS tunnel is dynamically signaled. If zero, the TLS tunnel is statically configured.

extremeMplsTlsType.name: extremeMplsTlsType
extremeMplsTlsType.description: The TLS tunnel type 0- MPLS, Static 1- MPLS, Martini .

extremeMplsTlsVcID.name: extremeMplsTlsVcID
extremeMplsTlsVcID.description: The configured VC ID, only valid if TLS tunnel is Dynamic. Otherwise, this field is set to zero.

extremeMplsTlsLocalGroupID.name: extremeMplsTlsLocalGroupID
extremeMplsTlsLocalGroupID.description: The configured Local Group ID, only valid if TLS tunnel is Dynamic. Otherwise, this field is set to zero.

extremeMplsTlsRemoteGroupID.name: extremeMplsTlsRemoteGroupID
extremeMplsTlsRemoteGroupID.description: The learned Remote Group ID, only valid if TLS tunnel is Dynamic. Otherwise, this field is set to zero.

extremeMplsTlsIngressVcLabel.name: extremeMplsTlsIngressVcLabel
extremeMplsTlsIngressVcLabel.description: The TLS tunnel VLAN Ingress Label. If the TLS tunnel is Static, this value is configured. If TLS tunnel is Dynamic, this value is dynamically allocated from the TLS label range and signaled to the TLS tunnel peer.

extremeMplsTlsEgressVcLabel.name: extremeMplsTlsEgressVcLabel
extremeMplsTlsEgressVcLabel.description: The TLS tunnel VLAN Egress Label. If the TLS tunnel is Static, this value is configured. If TLS tunnel is Dynamic, this value is learned from the TLS tunnel peer.

extremeMplsTlsVcState.name: extremeMplsTlsVcState
extremeMplsTlsVcState.description: The TLS tunnel VC state. Valid states include: - Idle - No LSP Available - Waiting for LDP session - Pending label mapping - Pending local configuration - MTU incompatibility - Up - Unknown - Error .. General failure - Error .. Targeted LDP session failure - Error .. Bridge configuration problem - Error .. Ingress label allocation failure - Error .. Failure sending TLS label mapping - Error .. Patricia tree insertion failure - Error .. Failure programming TLS hardware - Error .. MPLS not initialized - Error .. Unknown.

extremeMplsTlsPacketTx.name: extremeMplsTlsPacketTx
extremeMplsTlsPacketTx.description: The number of Packets Transmitted on this TLS tunnel.

extremeMplsTlsPacketRx.name: extremeMplsTlsPacketRx
extremeMplsTlsPacketRx.description: The number of Packets Received on this TLS tunnel.

extremeMplsTlsOctetTx.name: extremeMplsTlsOctetTx
extremeMplsTlsOctetTx.description: The number of Octets Transmitted on this TLS tunnel.

extremeMplsTlsOctetRx.name: extremeMplsTlsOctetRx
extremeMplsTlsOctetRx.description: The number of Octets Received on this TLS tunnel.
